SIMPLE: relevant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relevant
<hw>Rel"e*vant</hw> <pr>(-v<it>a</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>relevant</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>relever</ets> to raise again, to
relieve. See <er>Relieve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relieving;
lending aid or support.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pownall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bearing upon, or properly applying to, the case in
hand; pertinent; applicable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Close and <qex>relevant</qex> arguments have very little hold on
the passions.</q> <rj><qau>Sydney Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>Sufficient to support the
cause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relevantly</ent>⟦br⟧
